name: Frank Fritz
summary: On Monday, Frank Fritz, a beloved co-host of the popular television series "American Pickers," passed away at the age of 60. His death was confirmed by TMZ, which reported that he was receiving hospice care and was surrounded by a costar at the time of his passing. Fritz, an Iowa native, became well-known for his role in the show, in which he and Mike Wolfe traveled across the United States searching for valuable antiques and collectibles. Numerous news outlets, including Des Moines Register, KWQC, ABC News, NBC News, Variety, CNN, KCCI Des Moines, The New York Times, and WHBF, reported on Fritz's passing, paying tribute to his work and expressing condolences to his family and friends.

name: Jimmy Carter
summary: Today marks the centennial birthday of former US President Jimmy Carter. Numerous news organizations are commemorating the occasion by reflecting on his life and legacy. The New York Times recognizes his unwavering dedication to humanitarian efforts, while TIME magazine highlights his love for America and his commitment to service. NPR provides a visual journey through Carter's decades-long career, showcasing key moments from his presidency and post-presidential work. Emory University, where he served as a distinguished professor, celebrates his century of life and his impact on the university and beyond. The Associated Press examines the significant changes Carter has witnessed and influenced in the United States and around the world. News outlets such as NBC News, State Affairs, PBS NewsHour, and The Bitter Southerner acknowledge Carter's milestone birthday and offer perspectives on his remarkable life and accomplishments.

name: Astros
summary: The Houston Astros face elimination after losing Game 1 of the AL Wild Card series to the Detroit Tigers. Despite a strong performance, the Astros fell short by a narrow margin. The series will move to Houston for Game 2, where the Astros will need to win to force a decisive Game 3. The Astros' success in night games has made scheduling of the Wild Card series frustrating, as both games will be played in the afternoon. Despite the early setback, the Astros have selected Justin Verlander as their starting pitcher for Game 2. The Tigers, led by a strong performance from Skubal, took control of Game 1. Experts predict a close series, with the Astros holding a slight edge. The series is poised for an exciting and potentially decisive Game 2.

name: Ken Page
summary: Ken Page, a prominent actor known for his roles on Broadway and in the entertainment industry, has passed away at the age of 70. Page's notable roles include Old Deuteronomy in the original Broadway production of "Cats" and the voice of Oogie Boogie in Tim Burton's "The Nightmare Before Christmas." He also starred in numerous Broadway productions, including "Hair" and "Ain't Misbehavin'." Page's death is a significant loss for the entertainment world, and his contributions to both Broadway and film will be remembered fondly.

The suspension is a significant blow to the Bills, who are considered to be one of the favorites to win the Super Bowl this season. Miller is a key member of the Bills' defense, and his absence will be felt on the field.

name: Joker 2
summary: The highly anticipated "Joker 2" garnered mixed reactions. IGN highlighted the "fantasy of love" between Joaquin Phoenix's Joker and Lady Gaga's Harley Quinn, but Beebom criticized it as a "musical disaster." The Courier Journal provided information on the premiere date, cast, and Lady Gaga's album, while Variety expressed doubts about "Joker 2" matching the box office success of its predecessor. Marca English revealed the release date and streaming details. Hollywood Reporter covered the red carpet premiere in London. Despite the hype, GAMINGbible reported that Batman fans were divided over the "wild ending." Deadline projected a global box office opening of $140 million. SlashFilm addressed the post-credits scene, while The National deemed "Joker 2" a "tedious, confused and resentful" sequel.

summary: National Taco Day is celebrated annually on the first Tuesday of October, offering various deals and promotions from popular taco chains.
